					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-643075#post-1975149</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-643075/scp-1728#post-1975149</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 23 Feb 2014 06:45:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Doctor GE Smith</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1786409</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I have to agree with Lumancer's post about dream logic, and like most readers (it seems), I disliked it until the backstory became apparent. I like it, but there are 2 flaws that are making me downvote. As Voct pointed out, there was no reason for it to be trapped in a tree. More important to me is this:</p> <blockquote> <p>It uses the butter it exudes to its advantage, sliding across nearly any surface at speeds of up to 34kph and leaving tracks of butter behind it.</p> </blockquote> <p>Sliding like a dairy Iceman is way too LOLFoundation, and not even LOL&#8230;maybe a little&#8230; but still, no.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
